      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Why are UART channel 1 pins P212 and P213 not working ?"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The pins P212 and P213 are used as external clock oscillator pins (XTAL/EXTAL pins) so they cannot be used from SCI UART channel 1 in the same time. If you want to use them as SCI channel 1 pins, you need to have a clock source different than XTAL. Please change accordingly on Clocks tab (you can change PLL source or clock source itself):"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "content": {
          "original_url": "https://en-support.renesas.com/api/attachments/action/1/74d8968a-d702-4fc5-8e93-14051488bdb7",
          "alt_text": "",
          "width": "1007",
          "height": "647",
          "local_path": "data/categories/ra_family/serial_communications_interface_(sci)/40375ca0f5a008a568e9fa5b7f1bccbd/images/4394c1e6fb557a06c886fa6c3937a557.png"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "A new blank project by default is using XTAL as clock source which is already on the EK-RA6M2."
      }
